Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7. Drain the @sweetcorn{150%g} in a #sieve{}. Peel and grate the @garlic cloves{2%cloves} (or use a #garlic press{}).

Cut the @sweet potato{1}(cut into small 1cm chunks, no need to peel) and pop them onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{}(for drizzling), season with @salt{} and @ground black pepper{}, then toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until golden and tender, ~{16-18%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

Meanwhile, melt the @butter{20%g} in a large #saucepan{} on medium heat. Once the pan is hot, add the corn and fry until golden, ~{2-3%minutes}.

In the meantime, pop half the @red kidney beans{1%400g can} and all their liquid into a #medium bowl{} and mash with a #potato masher{}.

Once the corn is golden, add the @chipotle paste{20%g} and garlic. Stir-fry for ~{1%minute}.

Stir in the @tomato passata{1}, @vegetable stock paste{10%g}, kidney beans (whole and mashed), @sugar{1.5%tsp} and @water{200%ml} for the sauce. Bring to the boil, then lower the heat and simmer until thickened, ~{5-7%minutes}. Stir occasionally.

Meanwhile, cut each @plain taco tortillas{4} (2 per person) into 8 triangles (use #scissors{} if easier). Place on another large baking tray in a single layer and drizzle with @oil{}(for drizzling). Season with @salt{} and @ground black pepper{}.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

Bake on the middle shelf in the oven until lightly golden brown and crisp, ~{5-7%minutes}.

> TIP: Keep an eye on them to make sure they colour evenly.

While everything cooks, crumble the @Greek style salad cheese{100%g} into small pieces.

Once roasted, stir the sweet potato through the soup. Season with @salt{} and @ground black pepper{}, then remove from the heat.

Share your chipotle sweet potato soup between your #bowls{}. Drizzle with the @soured cream{75%g} and gently swirl it into the soup if you'd like.

Sprinkle over the cheese to finish and serve your tortilla dippers alongside. Enjoy!